01:07.372 --> 01:08.624
Thank you, sir.

01:11.416 --> 01:12.748
Sir!

01:13.456 --> 01:17.248
- You paid two zents less.
- Don't have change.

01:18.080 --> 01:20.124
Two zents!

01:20.456 --> 01:23.080
You dirty Korean!

01:23.416 --> 01:26.748
Two zents? Say it right,
two cents, moron!

01:29.292 --> 01:31.164
You owe me money!

01:31.500 --> 01:34.040
Get off me, you scum.

01:34.372 --> 01:37.372
This is Japan.
Go home if you don't like it.

01:37.708 --> 01:39.054
Go back to your damn country!

01:39.208 --> 01:40.663
Give me my money!

01:40.664 --> 01:41.664
Go back.

01:41.832 --> 01:43.580
Give me my fucking money.

01:51.040 --> 01:53.708
Be grateful that you can
make money in Japan.

01:56.832 --> 01:58.292
Fuck you!

02:00.956 --> 02:04.040
<i>I'm only a damn dog.</i>

02:05.832 --> 02:08.708
<i>From a nobleman's crotch,</i>

02:09.039 --> 02:12.916
<i>something hot pours out
bathing me all over,</i>

02:13.248 --> 02:18.708
<i>and I let a jet of hot water onto his legs.</i>

02:20.124 --> 02:23.916
<i>- Damn Dog -
I'm only a damn dog.</i>

02:29.208 --> 02:30.208
Hey.

02:31.040 --> 02:32.956
Who wrote this poem?

02:35.416 --> 02:36.872
<i>Damn Dog.</i>

02:43.664 --> 02:45.164
What are you doing?

02:46.708 --> 02:48.916
It says "I'm a damn dog".

02:49.080 --> 02:50.623
The Damn Dog must be the poet

02:50.624 --> 02:52.332
I'm serious.

02:53.416 --> 02:54.832
Park Yeol.

02:55.789 --> 02:58.687
He's the craziest Korean rebel in Japan.

02:59.414 --> 03:02.124
Parku... Yeoru?

03:02.164 --> 03:04.040
What? You just called him a fool.

03:04.164 --> 03:06.539
I didn't say that.

03:06.540 --> 03:09.292
Say it right. Park Yeol.

03:09.903 --> 03:11.027
Parku Yeoru.

03:11.764 --> 03:13.808
Getting close. Say it again.

03:13.932 --> 03:14.600
Parku Yeoru.

03:14.601 --> 03:17.224
- Almost there, one more time.
- Parku Yeoru!

03:18.180 --> 03:19.639
I got it right.

03:19.640 --> 03:21.724
Forget it. You never got closer.

03:22.724 --> 03:25.972
There comes the damn dog. Hey, Yeol!

03:30.472 --> 03:36.391
You are the craziest Korean rebel,

03:36.392 --> 03:40.600
Parku... Yol?

03:42.556 --> 03:44.263
Is she Japanese or Korean?

03:44.264 --> 03:46.100
Somewhere between.

03:47.100 --> 03:48.807
I'm Kaneko Fumiko.

03:48.808 --> 03:51.516
My Korean name is Mun-ja.

03:51.680 --> 03:52.680
Mun-ja?

03:53.392 --> 03:54.867
<i>Monthly Magazine
"Young Korean"</i>

03:54.892 --> 03:57.016
Oh, Damn Dog!

03:57.724 --> 03:59.516
How did you know?

04:00.224 --> 04:05.724
You're the 8th woman who
came to me after reading it.

04:06.892 --> 04:07.892
Wait!

04:09.100 --> 04:13.680
Do you have a spouse?

04:16.055 --> 04:17.724
I mean...

04:19.764 --> 04:22.971
If you have one,

04:22.972 --> 04:29.056
I don't mind just being your comrade.

04:30.140 --> 04:31.472
What do you think?

04:37.607 --> 04:41.939
Well, I'm single.

04:46.056 --> 04:47.808
Let's live together.

04:49.808 --> 04:51.556
I'm an anarchist, too.

04:53.848 --> 04:54.848
Let's go.

04:55.516 --> 04:56.516
Okay.

04:59.308 --> 05:02.724
How old are you?

05:04.224 --> 05:05.472
Twenty.

05:08.932 --> 05:12.100
Let me sit on it once in a while.

05:14.264 --> 05:16.640
Who is she?

05:17.348 --> 05:21.348
Why? Any hard feelings against Japanese?

05:22.140 --> 05:24.847
I'm against Japanese authorities,

05:24.848 --> 05:27.516
not the Japanese people.

05:43.140 --> 05:45.056
Fumiko.

06:07.972 --> 06:11.875
Nitric acid 75%, charcoal
15% and sulfur 10%.

06:14.132 --> 06:16.007
We followed the formula. What's wrong?

06:16.008 --> 06:20.300
Look at the color.
You put too much charcoal.

06:21.672 --> 06:25.424
Then, is charcoal 70% and sulfur 15%?

06:26.424 --> 06:30.216
This stupid bomb makes me explode.

06:30.508 --> 06:32.380
Any news from Shanghai?

06:33.380 --> 06:35.340
It will come soon.

06:35.924 --> 06:40.924
How can we get nitroglycerin?

06:55.092 --> 06:58.008
We know you stole the
campaign money from Russia.

06:58.185 --> 06:59.017
Who are you?

06:59.042 --> 07:00.042
We are...

07:04.756 --> 07:05.924
I mean we are...

07:08.300 --> 07:10.840
What's our group name again?

07:13.008 --> 07:14.008
Guys?

07:15.500 --> 07:18.371
<i>Patriots</i> until yesterday.

07:18.372 --> 07:20.540
From today, we're <i>Smashers.</i>

07:22.624 --> 07:26.872
You idiots. Do you know who I am?

07:27.164 --> 07:29.871
First chief editor
of Northeast Asia Daily,

07:29.872 --> 07:31.332
Kim Sung-cheol.

07:32.664 --> 07:35.664
Where's the campaign money?

07:36.832 --> 07:39.080
None of your business.

07:39.748 --> 07:43.664
Hey, smart ass. You think we're dumbheads?

07:44.416 --> 07:46.291
You think you're a big shot,

07:46.292 --> 07:50.040
just because you gave a
big independence speech?

07:50.065 --> 07:52.689
Is that why you're
treating us like idiots?

07:53.000 --> 07:58.664
You fools know nothing
about international politics

07:59.040 --> 08:03.039
Russian socialism
and Wilson's nationalism,

08:03.040 --> 08:04.011
After March 1st movement...

08:04.036 --> 08:05.580
Shut your fucking mouth.

08:05.792 --> 08:09.664
We can't even afford a damn bomb.

08:10.000 --> 08:13.623
You were gonna run away
with that money, right?

08:13.624 --> 08:17.080
You ignorant Koreans
have no idea...

08:19.080 --> 08:20.332
You son of a bitch.

08:21.208 --> 08:24.292
You're that smart to walk
away with that money?

08:29.080 --> 08:30.124
Let's do it.

08:35.539 --> 08:36.416
Move! Move!

08:36.539 --> 08:37.539
It's my turn.

08:43.832 --> 08:44.748
Table by the window.

08:44.749 --> 08:46.579
- Okay.
- Thanks.

08:46.580 --> 08:49.164
The food is coming.

08:51.332 --> 08:54.915
Here it is. Fishball soup.

08:54.916 --> 08:59.164
Sugimoto ran away, so that bomb is gone

09:00.872 --> 09:06.580
Kim was arrested, so the
Shanghai plan's screwed.

09:07.248 --> 09:11.708
We made it by ourselves,
but that didn't work

09:12.040 --> 09:13.208
I've got an idea.

09:13.664 --> 09:14.792
What's that?

09:16.332 --> 09:20.831
Each pharmacy sells 0.02
grams of explosives.

09:20.832 --> 09:26.916
Let's hit 100 pharmacies,
then we can make a real bomb.

09:27.040 --> 09:30.664
That's a brilliant idea.

09:32.372 --> 09:35.747
Do you even have money
to go around the city?

09:35.748 --> 09:37.999
Let's rob pro-japanese businessmen.

09:38.000 --> 09:40.832
And use that money on the road?

09:41.708 --> 09:43.791
Use your brain, dumb head.

09:43.792 --> 09:46.580
You just called me dumb? What the fuck!

09:49.248 --> 09:51.663
Hey hey, take it easy. Come down.

09:51.664 --> 09:53.292
Okay, okay.

09:54.000 --> 09:56.623
Fumiko, bring something for these pricks.

09:56.624 --> 09:57.624
Got it.

09:59.332 --> 10:02.248
Any news from Shanghai?

10:02.332 --> 10:04.872
I'll pick up the bomb when they're ready.

10:08.456 --> 10:13.248
Look at those commies, they're
up to something again.

10:13.580 --> 10:17.832
We should wipe out those rubbish Koreans.

10:18.164 --> 10:22.124
Please be quiet, we have customers.

10:22.555 --> 10:24.347
Who the fuck are you?

10:24.372 --> 10:26.055
Are you fucking Korean, too?

10:26.080 --> 10:29.956
Behave like a civilized citizen.

10:32.832 --> 10:34.832
Let go of me.

10:35.124 --> 10:36.332
Stop it.

10:37.055 --> 10:38.183
Give me a knife.

10:38.208 --> 10:40.292
Get off me.

10:43.872 --> 10:46.975
How dare you wield a sword!
You pathetic punks.

10:47.580 --> 10:51.291
Hot, right? Fuck off, you jerks.

10:51.292 --> 10:54.748
Still playing samurai, huh?

10:55.164 --> 10:57.708
You want me to cut off your topknot?

10:58.027 --> 10:59.691
You son of a bitch.

11:03.580 --> 11:05.416
Fuck off, you asshole.

11:05.792 --> 11:06.916
Scared now?

11:08.372 --> 11:11.332
You'll pay for this!

11:11.416 --> 11:12.708
Get 'em!

11:18.908 --> 11:21.864
That was our soup.

11:23.895 --> 11:25.683
This worked better for kicking out

11:25.708 --> 11:27.608
those dumb imperialists.

11:31.080 --> 11:34.332
It's called "Socialist
Fishball Soup" anyway.

11:34.559 --> 11:36.183
Will that be enough?

11:36.208 --> 11:39.579
Hey, why don't we throw Fumiko at them?

11:39.580 --> 11:43.624
Right, Fumiko. You'll be a fantastic bomb.

11:43.956 --> 11:44.624
Me?

11:44.664 --> 11:46.248
Come on, Ms. Bomb.

11:48.872 --> 11:54.956
Here's our secret weapon!
Kaneko Fumiko bomb!

11:58.443 --> 11:59.443
Hasuyo.

11:59.639 --> 12:02.223
- What's going on?
- Nothing.

12:02.248 --> 12:04.017
- Something happened?
- Come here.

12:04.042 --> 12:05.458
Fumiko bomb is useless.

12:07.766 --> 12:09.682
Park, have a good time!

12:10.456 --> 12:13.540
<i>"An Appeal to the Young"</i> - Kropotkin.

12:14.037 --> 12:15.161
Have you read this?

12:15.416 --> 12:18.475
Bourgeoisie go on honeymoons
to celebrate their wedding.

12:18.632 --> 12:21.424
Why don't we publish a book, instead?

12:21.664 --> 12:23.664
Kropotkin...

12:24.573 --> 12:25.821
Wait.

12:28.072 --> 12:30.947
I have <i>"The Conquest of Bread".</i>

12:30.948 --> 12:32.864
Why don't we translate it together?

12:33.156 --> 12:36.116
There's a translation for that already

12:36.492 --> 12:38.779
I don't wanna publish an existing book.

12:38.780 --> 12:42.200
Why don't we try writing our own?

12:53.700 --> 12:55.364
- Park!
- Yeah.

12:57.408 --> 12:59.572
- Come here - Why?

13:03.116 --> 13:04.240
What's that?

13:05.864 --> 13:08.031
<i>- Cohabitation agreement -</i>

13:08.032 --> 13:13.156
Do we really need this?
We can just live together.

13:13.908 --> 13:14.948
Stamp it.

13:16.780 --> 13:17.572
Are you sure?

13:17.572 --> 13:18.572
Yes.

13:24.072 --> 13:25.408
You won't regret?

13:26.072 --> 13:27.072
Never.

13:31.492 --> 13:33.072
Stop it.

13:37.200 --> 13:38.200
That's it.

13:40.364 --> 13:41.616
You stamp it too.

13:55.116 --> 13:57.991
A Japanese anarchist
sent some money to us.

13:57.992 --> 14:02.780
A Japanese anarchist sent some money to us.
<i>- Treason -</i>

14:07.364 --> 14:08.364
Read it.

14:11.556 --> 14:16.224
"I'm just a wanderer in
Korea, asking for bread.

14:16.740 --> 14:21.992
I'm sending small donation
to help your campaign.

14:22.593 --> 14:25.217
I hope this can be a little help".

14:25.572 --> 14:29.656
We have some ad revenues.

14:29.824 --> 14:31.615
Let's stop taking donation.

14:31.616 --> 14:33.700
Just say thank you, moron.

14:34.700 --> 14:36.280
The more, the better.

14:38.824 --> 14:39.908
Are you okay?

14:48.032 --> 14:50.324
OK, then let's take it.

14:51.608 --> 14:56.400
So, our topic of the day is...

14:56.608 --> 15:00.148
Should we beat up the journalist Jang

15:00.356 --> 15:02.608
who denounced socialists?

15:02.692 --> 15:05.023
What do you think?

15:05.024 --> 15:08.191
We know what to do. Who was...

15:08.192 --> 15:13.023
- Remember the guy the other day?
- The chief editor?

15:13.024 --> 15:16.272
We should beat him up like the last time.

15:16.856 --> 15:17.856
Hasuyo.

15:19.356 --> 15:21.524
Your boyfriend can beat him up.

15:23.608 --> 15:26.900
Leave it, Hasuyo. They're not fighting.

15:28.732 --> 15:32.316
How come you guys squabble all the time?

15:36.356 --> 15:40.400
I forgot what I was talking
about, you stupid morons.

15:40.940 --> 15:43.771
- Beating.
- Right, beating.

15:43.772 --> 15:45.856
So, you're all for beating?

15:48.192 --> 15:49.400
Wait.

15:51.356 --> 15:56.772
Do we really need to beat him
for denouncing socialists?

15:57.272 --> 16:00.980
We're not a reckless gang, are we?

16:04.440 --> 16:08.856
Anarchists should behave
according to their own will.

16:09.356 --> 16:10.356
Sure.

16:10.608 --> 16:13.440
Actions must be taken
according to individual will.

16:14.524 --> 16:15.979
I agree.

16:15.980 --> 16:21.148
Those of you who agree
can beat him up as you wish.

16:28.564 --> 16:29.564
Jung-han.

16:32.108 --> 16:34.524
Let's cancel the plan to Shanghai.

16:35.440 --> 16:36.980
Why? You told me to go.

16:37.192 --> 16:39.772
Do you hang with Hasuyo often?

16:43.980 --> 16:45.232
Once in a while. Why?

16:46.272 --> 16:48.399
Did you tell her you're going to Shanghai?

16:48.400 --> 16:51.732
What's she have to do
with me bringing bombs?

16:52.064 --> 16:54.608
Don't go. The plan is canceled.

16:58.608 --> 16:59.816
You don't trust me?

17:04.400 --> 17:06.271
Of course, I trust you.

17:06.771 --> 17:08.900
- It's just I wasn't cautious.
- Bullshit.

17:10.271 --> 17:11.856
You don't trust me.

17:12.480 --> 17:13.316
Jung-han...

17:13.340 --> 17:16.344
Park, what's wrong?

17:17.771 --> 17:19.647
- Hey.
- Hasuyo, let's go!

17:39.272 --> 17:40.316
Park.

17:43.816 --> 17:48.440
Why didn't you tell me about the bomb?

17:48.940 --> 17:51.732
I was going to tell you once I have it.

17:53.400 --> 17:56.732
You make all those plans
and leave me out of them?

17:57.356 --> 17:58.979
No, listen to me.

17:58.980 --> 18:00.900
Read that agreement again.

18:02.192 --> 18:05.980
If you don't count me as your comrade,

18:07.108 --> 18:09.108
I can't be with you.

18:09.980 --> 18:10.980
All right.

18:14.692 --> 18:16.816
Damn, it hurts.

18:34.016 --> 18:35.016
Stop right there.

18:36.750 --> 18:39.180
Don't eat it, it's for sale.

18:40.848 --> 18:43.140
This is for your own good too.

18:45.264 --> 18:47.100
What about your work?

18:47.348 --> 18:49.100
Why are you fooling around?

18:50.140 --> 18:52.764
I quit. I fought with a customer.

18:54.180 --> 18:57.392
Leftover newspapers?
I'll go sell them off.

19:02.224 --> 19:04.808
This one is strong. Cover the ginseng.

19:56.100 --> 19:57.808
Sir, are you all right?

19:58.140 --> 20:00.531
The new prime minister
hasn't been appointed.

20:00.556 --> 20:03.359
The Minister of Foreign Affairs
will chair the meeting

20:11.140 --> 20:14.392
11:59 a.m. today,

20:14.756 --> 20:23.256
an earthquake of magnitude 7.9
hit Kanto area including Tokyo.

20:23.600 --> 20:31.680
We reckon over 0.1 million died,
and 0.2 million lost their houses.

20:32.264 --> 20:37.516
And property loss will
cost up to 10 billion yen.

20:38.016 --> 20:39.516
Why is it so hot here?

20:40.972 --> 20:45.600
There's fire all over Tokyo.
It's 46°C outside.

20:47.016 --> 20:49.680
Army Chief, what's the recovery plan?

20:50.016 --> 20:55.432
The situation is grim, but
we'll do our very best.

20:55.964 --> 20:57.964
How long will it take?

20:58.840 --> 21:01.800
Sir, I am Army Chief

21:02.172 --> 21:06.048
I believe that can be answered
by the Interior Minister...

21:09.216 --> 21:12.132
Recovery isn't our priority.

21:12.548 --> 21:14.800
What's the priority then?

21:15.632 --> 21:20.672
We need countermeasures first.

21:25.256 --> 21:26.256
Fumiko!

21:29.340 --> 21:30.716
We're okay.

21:32.300 --> 21:35.632
Thank God

21:36.592 --> 21:38.008
I'm relieved.

21:39.340 --> 21:41.632
It's all crazy now.

21:42.132 --> 21:43.755
It's only an earthquake.

21:43.756 --> 21:46.048
Don't make a fuss.

21:46.592 --> 21:51.464
I mean people are at the Imperial Palace,

21:51.716 --> 21:54.464
demanding measures to be made.

21:54.548 --> 21:57.132
It might lead to a riot in a minute.

21:57.508 --> 22:01.716
Riot? How exciting!!

22:02.340 --> 22:05.508
They won't let a riot happen.

22:05.924 --> 22:06.924
Who?

22:08.216 --> 22:11.840
The emperor and his gangs.

22:21.048 --> 22:23.840
Once again, appointed
by his majesty the King

22:24.172 --> 22:26.464
as Prime Minister,

22:27.632 --> 22:30.092
Yamamoto Gonnohyoe.

22:34.132 --> 22:37.216
Minister of Interior, enlighten
us with your measures

22:38.880 --> 22:43.048
I've just been appointed today...

22:43.632 --> 22:48.008
How about hearing from the
former Minister of Interior?

23:00.924 --> 23:06.840
Hundreds of people were gathered around.

23:07.172 --> 23:10.300
Yasukuni Shrine and Ueno Park.

23:11.300 --> 23:13.755
Before they begin the riot,

23:13.756 --> 23:16.424
we need to impose martial law.

23:16.880 --> 23:23.632
Martial law can be imposed
only in wartime or civil war.

23:23.964 --> 23:26.924
Have you forgotten the
rice riot 5 years ago?

23:27.300 --> 23:31.424
Martial law without reason
might trigger a civil war.

23:32.132 --> 23:34.300
Of course, we have a reason.

23:36.008 --> 23:38.092
What do you mean?

23:40.940 --> 23:43.772
Koreans are poisoning the wells in town.

23:46.856 --> 23:49.856
What are you talking about?

23:51.480 --> 23:55.272
In this chaos, Koreans are poisoning wells

23:55.608 --> 23:59.108
and setting fire everywhere.

23:59.692 --> 24:03.856
Who told you that?

24:06.323 --> 24:08.363
Someone told me.

24:10.207 --> 24:12.831
You were bombed and dismissed

24:12.856 --> 24:15.816
after March 1st Movement in Korea, 1919.

24:16.564 --> 24:21.480
Aren't you saying those things

24:21.900 --> 24:27.272
out of personal anger and
hatred against Koreans?

24:30.356 --> 24:33.064
Does it really matter now?

24:33.900 --> 24:38.024
What matters is that they're
poisoning our wells.

24:40.480 --> 24:44.272
In the wake of the earthquake,
Koreans are setting fire,

24:44.608 --> 24:50.900
throwing bombs at major
facilities and officials.

24:51.638 --> 24:54.554
Minister of Justice,
what if a riot occurs?

24:54.772 --> 24:59.064
Will you take the blame?

25:01.892 --> 25:09.392
Who'll calm down the angry
crowds in front of the palace?

25:09.724 --> 25:12.972
Shouldn't we protect his majesty the King?

25:13.308 --> 25:14.516
Otherwise!

25:17.972 --> 25:20.972
We'll be the target.

25:29.892 --> 25:33.972
I appoint Army Chief Yamanashi

25:34.308 --> 25:37.056
as the martial law commander.

25:37.386 --> 25:38.386
Yes, sir!

25:38.764 --> 25:42.567
Former Interior Minister Mizuno,

25:43.556 --> 25:46.432
Emergency Chief, and Police Commissioner!

25:46.613 --> 25:53.180
You're in charge of relief
works and public order.

25:53.600 --> 25:54.600
Yes, sir!

25:56.264 --> 26:02.140
<i>Martial law is declared
as of 6 p.m., September 2nd.</i>

26:02.808 --> 26:08.931
<i>A number of Korean rebels
are mustering radicals.</i>

26:08.932 --> 26:17.348
<i>Veterans association, firefighters,
and young men's associations</i>

26:17.640 --> 26:22.348
<i>should stay vigilant and take
measures in contingencies.</i>

26:26.180 --> 26:28.056
Fifteen bucks, fifty cents.

26:28.640 --> 26:29.891
Say it.

26:29.892 --> 26:31.472
Don't be afraid.

26:31.764 --> 26:33.348
Say it.

