32:59.832 --> 33:00.832
Jin-yu!

33:01.708 --> 33:02.708
Fumiko?

33:04.080 --> 33:05.580
How are you doing, guys?

33:05.872 --> 33:08.580
What are you doing here?

33:09.832 --> 33:11.416
I'm one of <i>The Revolt,</i> too.

33:11.792 --> 33:13.956
So, you voluntarily walked in?

33:14.624 --> 33:15.624
That's right.

33:18.164 --> 33:19.956
You're nuts.

33:25.124 --> 33:26.624
I'm here too.

33:35.164 --> 33:36.164
Park.

33:37.664 --> 33:38.664
Yeah?

33:40.416 --> 33:42.372
I can't find Hasuyo.

33:43.332 --> 33:44.664
How about Jung-han?

33:45.040 --> 33:46.832
He said he'd go back to Korea.

33:48.372 --> 33:50.208
Don't worry.

33:51.208 --> 33:54.872
They're both our members, too.

33:57.248 --> 34:02.080
The other day, she asked
me to quit <i>The Revolt.</i>

34:03.040 --> 34:05.372
She said it's all useless.

34:06.248 --> 34:10.540
- What did you tell her?
- I didn't say a word.

34:11.916 --> 34:13.916
I slapped her in the face.

34:16.000 --> 34:17.956
<i>Setagaya Police Station</i>

34:19.040 --> 34:23.792
<i>Who was your target?</i>

34:23.916 --> 34:25.331
Tell me.

34:36.956 --> 34:38.040
Give me the name.

34:55.208 --> 34:59.540
Old habits die hard, huh?

35:17.580 --> 35:21.164
When I bring a bomb from Shanghai,

35:22.372 --> 35:25.040
Park Yeol said he'd throw it.

35:26.916 --> 35:28.164
Are you happy now?

35:30.208 --> 35:33.080
For the revolution to happen,

35:35.080 --> 35:37.208
they said

35:38.637 --> 35:41.792
this autumn is perfect.

35:43.580 --> 35:44.832
Are you sure?

35:47.372 --> 35:48.664
All right.

35:53.527 --> 35:56.027
We've got detailed statements.

35:56.164 --> 35:58.872
They didn't torture him, did they?

36:01.248 --> 36:05.832
- They...
- No torture, right?

36:09.416 --> 36:12.039
They never laid hands on him.

36:12.040 --> 36:13.872
Good...

36:14.812 --> 36:16.144
So,

36:17.116 --> 36:19.199
A group called <i>The Revolt</i>

36:19.200 --> 36:22.864
tried to buy a bomb from Shanghai?

36:23.200 --> 36:26.200
Did they get it or not?

36:26.948 --> 36:29.072
It seems like they failed, sir.

36:30.572 --> 36:32.864
They might have obtained it.

36:34.616 --> 36:36.156
So...

36:37.364 --> 36:40.656
What was their target?

36:42.780 --> 36:45.700
They planned for this autumn.

36:48.492 --> 36:53.864
Do we have any event in the autumn?

36:55.780 --> 36:57.864
Who's the leader?

37:03.908 --> 37:05.408
Minister of Justice Hiranuma.

37:07.364 --> 37:11.364
We have a big project for you.

37:12.616 --> 37:14.992
Have you heard about <i>The Revolt?</i>

37:15.324 --> 37:21.908
Isn't that a group of socialist
Koreans living in Japan?

37:22.332 --> 37:27.780
We use the word "rebels"
to call unruly Koreans.

37:28.116 --> 37:32.200
Now, they named their
group after that word.

37:33.324 --> 37:36.824
They're clearly mocking us.

37:38.948 --> 37:42.864
I want you to take this case.

37:47.780 --> 37:50.032
I'll do my best, sir.

37:51.200 --> 37:52.863
Prosecute them and

37:52.864 --> 37:56.532
interrogate them with justice.

37:57.240 --> 37:58.324
Yes, sir.

37:59.908 --> 38:02.364
Make it reasonable,

38:02.793 --> 38:08.832
but the conclusion is decided.

38:12.032 --> 38:13.116
Excuse me?

38:14.200 --> 38:19.740
A conclusion that Korean
socialists erupted riots

38:20.072 --> 38:25.240
in the confusion following the earthquake.

38:30.864 --> 38:32.364
Setting me free already?

38:32.864 --> 38:34.364
You're going to the prison.

38:36.280 --> 38:37.740
For what crime?

38:38.364 --> 38:42.200
You are charged with a
violation of security law.

38:43.864 --> 38:45.532
Is that it?

38:47.324 --> 38:49.156
Get off me.

38:49.532 --> 38:51.448
I'll go by myself.

38:55.116 --> 38:58.116
Why do you take him alone? What about us?

38:58.448 --> 39:00.908
Don't know. I only follow orders.

39:03.616 --> 39:05.364
Don't tag along this time.

39:07.116 --> 39:08.448
Understood?

39:13.840 --> 39:18.340
Take me with him! I did it too!

39:20.256 --> 39:22.048
You did what?

39:22.450 --> 39:23.964
Whatever.

39:26.172 --> 39:28.172
Take me, too!

39:28.840 --> 39:32.800
