39:55.092 --> 39:58.964
♪ <i>And spurn the dust to win the prize</i> ♪

39:59.300 --> 40:01.592
♪ <i>So comrades, come rally!</i> ♪

40:03.672 --> 40:07.592
Korean Rebels Arrested

40:08.300 --> 40:12.380
for Attempted Assassin of

40:13.132 --> 40:17.800
Government Official in Tokyo.

40:21.800 --> 40:29.300
Now that press control
of the massacre is lifted,

40:29.632 --> 40:32.964
The first news to come up is.

40:33.172 --> 40:36.172
"Arrest of the Secret Korean Organization."

40:39.400 --> 40:40.856
Mizuno!

40:42.400 --> 40:44.732
Was this your idea?

40:45.064 --> 40:47.440
I think Heaven helped us.

40:52.940 --> 40:56.024
We declared that Koreans started a riot,

40:57.648 --> 40:59.732
without any evidence.

41:02.192 --> 41:06.564
That could've caused us a problem, right?

41:07.524 --> 41:12.400
Now, here we have the evidence.

41:12.863 --> 41:20.130
They did plan to buy a bomb
to kill a government official.

41:26.440 --> 41:28.855
Welcome to Ichigaya prison,

41:28.856 --> 41:32.480
The door won't open until you die.

41:32.816 --> 41:37.480
The door will open soon.
Wanna bet on your emperor?

41:41.024 --> 41:43.271
What a lunatic.

41:43.272 --> 41:45.480
No, you're a lunatic.

41:45.692 --> 41:48.192
You think your emperor is God?

41:49.618 --> 41:50.618
What?

41:52.900 --> 41:58.400
He's only a human. He pees and poos.

41:58.732 --> 42:02.940
And he's fucking short like a dwarf.

42:08.980 --> 42:10.648
See?

42:10.980 --> 42:12.900
I told you it'll open.

42:17.907 --> 42:21.155
Isn't it nice here? We can eat and sleep.

42:21.272 --> 42:22.899
- Fumiko, see you later.
- Yes.

42:22.900 --> 42:25.349
- Count the stars to sleep.
- Okay.

42:27.316 --> 42:30.192
Fumiko, eat well.

42:38.232 --> 42:40.400
You must be crazier,

42:40.732 --> 42:44.608
to come here for that lunatic.

42:45.732 --> 42:46.856
My room?

43:05.272 --> 43:09.192
Don't be nervous. Have a seat

43:09.480 --> 43:13.064
I'm not nervous. Are you?

43:15.816 --> 43:17.272
This is my seat?

43:21.184 --> 43:24.932
Can you speak Japanese?

43:25.242 --> 43:29.410
I can, but I'll only speak Korean.

43:31.948 --> 43:36.156
This is a courtroom in Japan.
You have to talk in Japanese.

43:38.656 --> 43:41.032
Then I won't say a word.

43:45.492 --> 43:46.700
Sit.

43:51.864 --> 43:55.780
It could bring you some disadvantage.

43:56.492 --> 43:58.240
You know Korean.

44:00.908 --> 44:02.324
You understand my words.

44:04.448 --> 44:06.072
Actually,

44:06.532 --> 44:08.532
I've learned it for a while.

44:09.780 --> 44:13.364
I know only one reason why
you people learn Korean.

44:13.740 --> 44:20.072
To work in the poor colony and
climb the ladder of success here?

44:21.072 --> 44:23.656
Don't judge me like that.

44:25.992 --> 44:30.156
You can make this a lot
easier by talking in Korean.

44:36.032 --> 44:39.240
Then let's use our own language.

44:42.656 --> 44:43.992
How old are you?

44:44.310 --> 44:45.740
Why are you asking?

44:45.948 --> 44:47.448
Come on, tell me.

44:49.616 --> 44:51.700
Thirty-one.

44:53.908 --> 44:55.408
Older than me.

44:56.908 --> 45:00.740
Feel free to talk down to me.

45:04.780 --> 45:08.072
If you say so.

45:08.408 --> 45:10.408
What's my charge?

45:15.215 --> 45:20.883
You've been charged for
mustering anarchists

45:20.908 --> 45:23.739
and organizing a secret group

45:23.740 --> 45:26.992
for armed socialist movement.

45:27.324 --> 45:30.032
Fujishita!

45:30.408 --> 45:31.740
Fujishita!

45:32.780 --> 45:33.864
Fujishita!

45:35.616 --> 45:37.072
What?

45:37.656 --> 45:38.992
Got a pen and paper?

45:39.740 --> 45:41.616
Writing your will already?

45:44.448 --> 45:47.656
I guess I'll write a letter of apology.

45:47.992 --> 45:49.532
Apology?

45:49.700 --> 45:52.779
You regret doing crazy things

45:52.780 --> 45:54.364
with that Korean dog, huh?

45:54.948 --> 45:58.280
I'll give you every detail

45:58.616 --> 46:00.992
about what I did with him.

46:03.992 --> 46:05.364
Name.

46:06.740 --> 46:08.324
Park Jun-sik.

46:08.572 --> 46:10.700
People call me Park Yeol.

46:12.310 --> 46:13.850
Age?

46:14.532 --> 46:16.616
9 years younger than you.

46:20.780 --> 46:22.448
Twenty-two.

46:22.532 --> 46:24.072
Occupation?

46:28.532 --> 46:31.656
Let's call it a magazine publisher.

46:32.700 --> 46:34.572
You can write that down.

46:39.072 --> 46:40.571
Address?

46:40.572 --> 46:45.656
1474 Yoyogi-tomigaya,
Toyotama District, Tokyo.

46:46.017 --> 46:47.601
Place of birth?

46:50.324 --> 46:55.864
98 Ocheon-ri, Mungyeong,
Gyeongsangbuk-do, Korea.

46:59.656 --> 47:02.408
Who are you living with?

47:05.913 --> 47:07.705
Kaneko Fumiko.

47:15.992 --> 47:18.948
Are you living with Park Yeol?

47:20.433 --> 47:21.225
Yes.

47:21.324 --> 47:23.408
Are you registered as his wife?

47:23.880 --> 47:25.256
No, I'm not.

47:25.656 --> 47:28.740
We both didn't want that.

47:29.072 --> 47:31.740
Why did you go to Korea?

47:32.116 --> 47:36.992
When I was 9, I went to my
grandma's to do housekeeping.

47:37.566 --> 47:39.814
Why was that?

47:44.780 --> 47:47.116
My parents abandoned me.

47:49.700 --> 47:54.492
When did you return to Japan?

47:55.200 --> 47:57.864
Right after March 1st Movement.

47:58.324 --> 48:00.324
How did you meet Park Yeol?

48:01.816 --> 48:03.272
<i>Damn Dog.</i>

48:03.816 --> 48:04.980
What's that?

48:08.648 --> 48:12.732
I read his poem <i>"Damn Dog"</i>

48:13.064 --> 48:15.400
and fell in love with him.

48:16.272 --> 48:20.440
<i>"Damn dog"</i> is the title of his poem?

48:20.816 --> 48:22.064
Right.

48:25.356 --> 48:26.356
All right.

48:27.608 --> 48:29.108
Damn dog.

48:33.772 --> 48:35.400
I was reciting the poem.

48:35.900 --> 48:37.856
Just answer my question.

48:38.816 --> 48:40.480
Okay, sir.

48:45.900 --> 48:49.232
You are the founder of <i>The Revolt?</i>

48:50.024 --> 48:51.024
That's right.

48:51.316 --> 48:55.272
<i>The Revolt</i> is a Korean socialist
group, is this correct?

48:56.108 --> 48:59.440
No, <i>The Revolt</i> is an anarchist group.

49:02.648 --> 49:05.024
And you're the leader of that group?

49:06.564 --> 49:07.648
That's correct.

49:12.524 --> 49:16.316
Were you leading the
plan to obtain a bomb?

49:26.064 --> 49:29.272
Bomb? What bomb?

49:30.816 --> 49:36.732
The bomb you asked Jung-han
to pick up from Shanghai.

49:41.192 --> 49:42.732
Let me ask you again.

49:42.980 --> 49:47.480
Did you set up the plan?

49:49.536 --> 49:53.856
Get me a lawyer, or
I won't say a single word.

49:57.856 --> 50:02.772
Were you aware of
Park's plan to get a bomb?

50:06.400 --> 50:07.772
Yes, I knew.

50:09.316 --> 50:10.564
Are you sure?

50:11.608 --> 50:16.108
Of course. We planned it together.

50:19.732 --> 50:23.648
Any specific venue or date?

50:26.064 --> 50:27.900
Just as Park said.

50:30.564 --> 50:33.148
He didn't say a word.

50:39.192 --> 50:40.316
Now...

50:48.648 --> 50:50.316
Get me a lawyer.

51:03.316 --> 51:05.732
Jung-han blew the bomb plan.

51:07.832 --> 51:08.956
I know.

51:12.064 --> 51:14.400
They'll frame us all.

51:15.108 --> 51:17.064
Someone needs to take the blame.

51:17.192 --> 51:19.024
- What?
- Someone?

51:19.732 --> 51:22.980
Are you saying you'll hold the bag?

51:23.108 --> 51:26.272
Jung-han mentioned only about me.

51:26.400 --> 51:32.524
None of you knew or heard
about the bomb, okay?

51:33.316 --> 51:36.564
What are you gonna do on your own?

51:38.608 --> 51:41.316
I'll be the hero as they planned.

51:49.564 --> 51:53.272
Shut the fuck up, dirty Koreans!

51:55.016 --> 51:57.308
From now on, I'll tell you everything.

51:58.556 --> 52:02.308
Who else was involved in the plan?

52:03.056 --> 52:05.432
Other members don't know about it.

52:06.848 --> 52:08.392
You planned it on your own?

52:09.600 --> 52:10.640
Correct.

52:15.100 --> 52:17.432
Who was the target?

52:19.392 --> 52:22.016
Your prince, Michinomiya.

52:24.056 --> 52:25.348
What did you say?

52:28.264 --> 52:35.848
Prince Hirohito's childhood name.
Ironically, "Michinomiya" means

52:36.016 --> 52:37.808
"crazy bitch" in Korean.

52:39.224 --> 52:44.180
Do you have any idea what
your statement means?

52:47.932 --> 52:53.264
I know for sure it'll be the
biggest case in your life.

52:54.224 --> 52:55.640
<i>Prime Minister,</i>

52:55.892 --> 52:57.892
an act of treason has occurred.

52:59.348 --> 53:00.348
What?

53:00.764 --> 53:02.867
Park Yeol, the leader of
the group <i>The Revolt,</i>

53:02.892 --> 53:06.180
planned to assassin Prince Hirohito.

53:06.516 --> 53:08.555
Is he alive?

53:08.556 --> 53:10.472
Yes, he's alive.

53:10.810 --> 53:14.100
How grateful! God protected our prince.

53:15.100 --> 53:17.348
Did the bullet miss him?

53:17.636 --> 53:19.823
It's not a bullet. It's a bomb.

53:19.848 --> 53:21.348
A bomb?

53:22.180 --> 53:24.016
It didn't go off?

53:24.041 --> 53:28.665
The d-day was the prince's wedding day.

53:29.016 --> 53:33.932
But the wedding was postponed
because of the earthquake.

53:34.224 --> 53:38.432
The earthquake saved the prince!

53:40.172 --> 53:45.172
So you're saying there
was only a conspiracy.

53:48.432 --> 53:51.556
If not the earthquake,
Park would have done it.

53:58.816 --> 54:03.272
Attempted assassin of the prince...

54:03.858 --> 54:05.274
This Korean...

54:06.100 --> 54:09.892
...actually tried to murder
the prince with a bomb.

54:10.224 --> 54:12.308
He's definitely a traitor!

54:17.048 --> 54:20.756
You have evidence and witnesses?

54:21.092 --> 54:23.880
We have his confession.

54:24.716 --> 54:30.672
Did you know Park was going to
throw a bomb at the prince?

54:33.508 --> 54:34.716
What did he say?

54:34.924 --> 54:38.840
- Answer the question.
- Answer me first.

54:40.964 --> 54:44.132
He said other members
didn't know about the plan.

54:47.048 --> 54:48.964
Any word about me?

54:57.763 --> 55:08.387
"My statement about Fumiko
might offend her feelings."

55:10.008 --> 55:13.380
"So I'll let her make
decisions on her own."

55:22.800 --> 55:23.840
Fumiko,

55:27.008 --> 55:32.840
I'm willing to help you as a Japanese.

55:33.256 --> 55:35.464
Did Park threaten you?

55:35.632 --> 55:38.716
Or, does he have something on you?

55:42.264 --> 55:44.888
I threatened him.

55:46.008 --> 55:47.172
What?

55:50.271 --> 55:54.592
I taught Park that we
don't need an emperor

55:54.924 --> 55:59.632
that we shouldn't have one
from the first place.

56:00.340 --> 56:02.132
In other words,

56:02.964 --> 56:04.592
I was his...

56:05.216 --> 56:07.508
private tutor.

56:09.308 --> 56:12.100
<i>Iron Fist, Smashers, Bloody Fists.</i>

56:12.424 --> 56:15.716
<i>Black Daggers, Black Comrades, The Revolt.</i>

56:17.424 --> 56:20.419
These are organizations
you've joined or made so far,

56:20.632 --> 56:22.132
right?

56:22.464 --> 56:25.964
Did I make that many?

56:26.092 --> 56:27.216
It seems to me,

56:27.424 --> 56:28.923
you're just eager to

56:28.924 --> 56:30.924
make yourself famous.

56:31.216 --> 56:32.548
Am I wrong?

56:36.172 --> 56:38.800
I only live for myself.

56:39.771 --> 56:41.300
What do you mean?

56:42.840 --> 56:46.924
I eat when I'm hungry.
I do it when I want it.

56:48.380 --> 56:49.840
Do it?

56:51.632 --> 56:52.840
Do what?

56:53.632 --> 56:55.424
Intercourse.

56:56.756 --> 56:57.964
Don't you know?

56:58.880 --> 57:02.132
To make love.

57:02.924 --> 57:05.424
Answer my questions seriously.

57:09.380 --> 57:11.132
Seriously?

57:16.548 --> 57:20.216
You wanna know why I tried
to kill the prince?

57:21.672 --> 57:26.508
Nation, people, monarch.

57:26.840 --> 57:30.756
These are only theoretical concepts.

57:31.092 --> 57:37.482
You gave power and holiness
to those mere concepts

57:37.592 --> 57:40.508
and created an emperor and prince.

57:44.916 --> 57:46.748
Humans,

57:47.164 --> 57:53.591
all of us are entitled to equal
rights as a human being.

57:53.664 --> 57:57.792
The very devils who destroy
the equal world are

57:58.124 --> 58:00.664
the Emperor and the Prince.

58:02.916 --> 58:04.248
Devils?

58:04.916 --> 58:07.164
Therefore,

58:08.416 --> 58:10.664
they shall be demolished.

58:12.792 --> 58:16.416
We're living with a parasite Emperor,

58:16.500 --> 58:20.792
who is harming the peace of mankind.

58:21.748 --> 58:23.164
Parasite?

58:23.580 --> 58:29.792
It's my dream to destroy not only Japan,

58:30.708 --> 58:32.916
but the whole fucking world.

58:46.792 --> 58:49.490
- What about Park?
- Why are we out?

58:51.956 --> 58:54.748
We're kicking you out, morons.

58:58.872 --> 59:01.580
Remember the attorney Huse?

59:02.248 --> 59:06.416
The pro bono lawyer
who defended us last time?

59:06.864 --> 59:08.784
Let's ask him one more time.

59:09.580 --> 59:10.624
Are you okay?

59:12.332 --> 59:15.708
This case will be much tougher than

59:16.040 --> 59:21.416
the previous laborer cases
like Choi and Baek.

59:22.411 --> 59:25.664
Please... we need your help, sir.

59:29.292 --> 59:33.124
They're likely to put them on a trial

59:33.456 --> 59:36.080
for a treason.

59:36.292 --> 59:39.956
Which means... a death penalty?

59:43.832 --> 59:47.040
We have to stop it from happening.

59:47.416 --> 59:49.208
Thank you very much.

59:57.248 --> 01:00:02.540
You must be busy defending labor workers.

01:00:03.040 --> 01:00:05.664
This case was clearly fabricated.

01:00:06.540 --> 01:00:08.208
I'll stop the prosecution.

01:00:08.708 --> 01:00:13.664
There's no need for it.
I've admitted my charge.

01:00:14.164 --> 01:00:16.748
Unlike political prisoners,

01:00:17.080 --> 01:00:19.372
traitors are punished only by death.

01:00:20.332 --> 01:00:25.208
Death penalty can't shut my mouth up.

01:00:29.456 --> 01:00:32.000
If you go too close to the truth,

01:00:32.332 --> 01:00:34.292
you'll get closer to death.

01:00:41.956 --> 01:00:46.580
Please withdraw your advocacy.

01:00:48.832 --> 01:00:55.664
You'll be the first Korean
charged with treason.

01:00:59.332 --> 01:01:00.748
Treason?

01:01:01.792 --> 01:01:04.872
It's treason to Japanese.

01:01:05.208 --> 01:01:10.292
But if this is what I
should do as a Korean,

01:01:10.624 --> 01:01:12.000
I'll be more than glad

01:01:13.456 --> 01:01:15.580
to be a traitor.

01:01:16.708 --> 01:01:19.540
<i>Destroy! Destroy everything!</i>

01:01:19.792 --> 01:01:22.624
<i>Set fire! Throw a bomb!</i>

01:01:22.832 --> 01:01:26.872
<i>Spread poison! Destroy the whole world.</i>

01:01:27.540 --> 01:01:33.164
I will wash out the world

01:01:33.500 --> 01:01:37.248
tainted by hideous mankind
in crimson blood.

01:01:37.580 --> 01:01:41.664
And I, too, will die in destruction.

01:01:42.500 --> 01:01:44.500
What a fucking lunatic.

01:01:45.708 --> 01:01:48.624
They both seem deranged.

01:01:49.824 --> 01:01:52.864
They should undergo a psychiatric
test before the trial.

01:01:55.032 --> 01:01:56.656
Psychiatric test?

01:01:57.572 --> 01:02:00.199
In the West, they let the criminals

01:02:00.200 --> 01:02:02.824
take the test before punishing them.

01:02:03.240 --> 01:02:05.992
What if the result says they're mad?

01:02:07.740 --> 01:02:10.532
I don't give a shit about their brain.

01:02:10.780 --> 01:02:13.740
Just make them normal, no matter what!

01:02:20.156 --> 01:02:23.448
The prince has been shot.

01:02:23.700 --> 01:02:25.280
<i>Police Commissioner!</i>

01:02:25.616 --> 01:02:27.992
Are you fucking out of your mind?

01:02:28.200 --> 01:02:33.364
Where the fuck were you when
the prince was attacked?

01:02:34.200 --> 01:02:38.280
Who shot him? A Korean? Who?

01:02:38.616 --> 01:02:43.492
It was Namba Diasuke, a son
of a house representative.

01:02:44.656 --> 01:02:47.824
Now even a lawmaker's son is a commie?

01:02:48.408 --> 01:02:51.824
Fucking commies are everywhere.

01:02:52.700 --> 01:02:55.864
It's my fault. I'll resign myself.

01:03:04.280 --> 01:03:07.324
<i>Namba Daisuke Fires a
Gun at Prince Hirohito.</i>

01:03:11.824 --> 01:03:14.824
Do you know the anarchist
called Namba Daisuke?

01:03:16.448 --> 01:03:20.072
I met him once at a protest on Labor Day.

01:03:21.240 --> 01:03:22.700
Did he shoot the prince?

01:03:22.992 --> 01:03:28.364
The shooter chanted "Revolution"
and fired at the prince's car.

01:03:31.023 --> 01:03:32.271
Was it successful?

01:03:34.216 --> 01:03:35.824
Failed.

01:03:37.948 --> 01:03:41.908
He should have thrown a
bomb, not a stupid gun.

01:03:48.572 --> 01:03:50.824
At least he put it into action.

01:03:51.364 --> 01:03:55.908
You never had guts for it.

01:03:56.616 --> 01:03:59.116
You couldn't even get a bomb.

01:04:01.700 --> 01:04:04.116
Take a psychiatric test first.

01:04:04.591 --> 01:04:06.407
Psychiatric test, my ass.

01:04:06.408 --> 01:04:08.492
And get a lawyer again.

01:04:08.572 --> 01:04:10.531
Charge me for treason!

01:04:10.532 --> 01:04:12.824
You don't fucking deserve it!

01:04:23.992 --> 01:04:30.115
As a result of the shooting,
Yamamoto Cabinet has resigned.

01:04:30.116 --> 01:04:32.215
And the next cabinet has been announced.

01:04:32.240 --> 01:04:34.864
Matsui as the Foreign Minister.

01:04:37.448 --> 01:04:40.448
Mizuno as the Interior Minister.

01:04:43.448 --> 01:04:45.780
Mizuno, this asshole.

01:04:47.700 --> 01:04:51.324
The murderer is in charge
of the internal affairs again.

01:04:52.636 --> 01:04:55.096
Is this the infamous socialist pub?

01:04:55.643 --> 01:04:56.767
Who are you?

01:04:57.732 --> 01:05:00.232
I'm a journalist from Korea.

01:05:05.024 --> 01:05:06.192
<i>Park Yeol and His Lover</i>

01:05:06.217 --> 01:05:08.692
Park's on the paper. I'm so proud of him.

01:05:08.732 --> 01:05:09.940
For what?

01:05:11.564 --> 01:05:13.024
He didn't achieve anything.

01:05:13.692 --> 01:05:16.024
He's just got a bad temper.

01:05:19.024 --> 01:05:20.316
Go on.

01:05:20.940 --> 01:05:24.648
Besides, I've heard rumors
about him and women.

01:05:24.900 --> 01:05:27.148
All these stories about
attracting women...

01:05:27.272 --> 01:05:28.272
What the fuck?

01:05:29.400 --> 01:05:31.024
You're a spy, aren't you?

01:05:31.192 --> 01:05:33.108
Go on with that rubbish!

01:05:38.940 --> 01:05:42.356
You're clearly speaking Korean

01:05:43.356 --> 01:05:47.272
but to me, it sounds like Japanese.

01:05:50.732 --> 01:05:53.900
People back home have
high expectations for Park.

01:05:55.232 --> 01:05:58.356
But he's letting the Japanese
cabinet take advantage of him.

01:05:58.564 --> 01:06:01.608
He even seems like he's enjoying it.

01:06:06.356 --> 01:06:09.692
Can't you see this case was designed

01:06:10.356 --> 01:06:12.480
to cover the Korean massacre?

01:06:20.192 --> 01:06:23.524
He needs to prove his innocence,

01:06:24.024 --> 01:06:25.772
but he willingly testified.

01:06:26.608 --> 01:06:29.024
Isn't he making a false confession?

01:06:29.608 --> 01:06:31.440
No, that's not true.

01:06:31.648 --> 01:06:33.940
You don't know anything.

01:06:34.940 --> 01:06:38.356
Park had a plan B to buy a bomb.

01:06:38.692 --> 01:06:39.692
What?

01:06:40.816 --> 01:06:42.064
Keep talking.

01:06:42.184 --> 01:06:46.016
A few days before the earthquake,

01:06:46.148 --> 01:06:49.648
we smuggled a bomb from Shanghai

01:06:49.900 --> 01:06:53.064
and brought it here in Tokyo.

01:06:54.732 --> 01:06:57.732
- So, you did get a bomb.
- Yes.

01:06:58.024 --> 01:07:01.564
- How can you be sure?
- I'm the one who delivered it.

01:07:01.816 --> 01:07:03.816
If not the earthquake,

01:07:03.856 --> 01:07:08.772
we'd have done it before Namba did.

01:07:14.692 --> 01:07:19.272
I wonder why Park never told me that.

01:07:23.232 --> 01:07:25.524
Is there anything you
guys are hiding from me?

01:07:25.608 --> 01:07:26.608
Hey.

01:07:27.148 --> 01:07:30.772
If I had a bomb, I'd
have thrown it already.

01:07:31.816 --> 01:07:32.816
And you?

01:07:35.272 --> 01:07:38.439
What are you guys talking about?

01:07:38.440 --> 01:07:39.856
Nothing.

01:07:40.732 --> 01:07:43.732
What are you guys, anyway?

01:07:44.192 --> 01:07:45.480
Us?

01:07:49.148 --> 01:07:50.316
<i>The Revolt!</i>

01:07:56.400 --> 01:07:59.772
Please give her this.

01:08:01.648 --> 01:08:04.272
<i>Emperor and prince are only humans.</i>

01:08:04.772 --> 01:08:08.316
<i>Locked inside the castle
and forced to be Gods.</i>

01:08:10.148 --> 01:08:15.356
<i>The Emperor and the prince are
no more than chunks of meat.</i>

01:08:16.192 --> 01:08:19.356
<i>It's not a big deal to
get rid of the prince.</i>

01:08:20.524 --> 01:08:24.479
<i>The emperor is ill and will die soon.</i>

01:08:25.648 --> 01:08:27.564
<i>Our target is the prince.</i>

01:08:28.732 --> 01:08:31.316
<i>Once we get rid of the prince,</i>

01:08:31.856 --> 01:08:35.899
<i>the Japanese will be enlightened.</i>

01:08:41.108 --> 01:08:42.899
You scared me.

01:08:45.392 --> 01:08:46.392
Hey!

01:08:48.015 --> 01:08:50.432
Where's her reply?

01:08:50.764 --> 01:08:54.680
Letters that breach moral ethics

01:08:55.640 --> 01:08:59.015
are censored and destroyed.

01:08:59.640 --> 01:09:05.015
It is the language that
unites me and Fumiko.

01:09:05.515 --> 01:09:11.179
By assuring each other our
thoughts haven't changed,

01:09:11.180 --> 01:09:12.848
we've completed our love.

01:09:13.308 --> 01:09:14.555
Listen.

01:09:15.264 --> 01:09:20.015
Countless commies gave
up their ideology here.

01:09:20.348 --> 01:09:22.892
You'll end up the same.

01:09:23.600 --> 01:09:29.848
You'll be grateful for His Majesty

01:09:30.180 --> 01:09:34.055
to have granted you as his subject.

01:09:37.140 --> 01:09:41.392
If you trash the letters again,

01:09:42.264 --> 01:09:45.680
I'm going on a hunger strike.

01:09:47.555 --> 01:09:51.055
How's the apology letter going?

01:09:51.392 --> 01:09:58.556
Everyone here is talking
about the pretty new girl.

01:10:00.308 --> 01:10:02.016
Thanks for the compliment.

01:10:03.392 --> 01:10:11.724
Lustful prisoners are asking
for the key to your cell.

01:10:17.516 --> 01:10:19.971
Kneel down before the emperor

01:10:19.972 --> 01:10:23.972
before you get raped by the barbarians.

01:10:30.392 --> 01:10:32.016
You come in first.

01:10:35.224 --> 01:10:41.016
I wonder what people will say about

01:10:41.348 --> 01:10:44.180
a fervent imperialist raping a prisoner.

01:10:46.224 --> 01:10:47.307
Put your clothes on.

01:10:47.308 --> 01:10:48.892
Come on.

01:10:49.224 --> 01:10:52.640
I'll make you a symbol of the brutality

01:10:52.972 --> 01:10:56.848
along with the Japanese Empire.

01:10:57.392 --> 01:10:59.472
Crazy bitch.

01:11:23.910 --> 01:11:25.034
Eat it.

01:11:40.764 --> 01:11:42.680
<i>Park Yeol on Hunger Strike in Prison</i>

01:11:42.764 --> 01:11:46.615
Are you still banning letters?
I told you to permit it.

01:11:47.172 --> 01:11:49.632
It is my job to censor them.

01:11:49.964 --> 01:11:53.424
Those letters full of anti-imperialism

01:11:53.756 --> 01:11:56.216
<i>are driving me insane.</i>

01:11:57.424 --> 01:11:59.008
Hunger strike?

01:12:00.340 --> 01:12:01.716
What does he want?

01:12:02.256 --> 01:12:04.672
Exchanging letters with Kaneko Fumiko.

01:12:05.924 --> 01:12:10.048
Let him have it, and
prosecute him for treason.

01:12:10.380 --> 01:12:12.256
Treason won't work, sir.

01:12:16.256 --> 01:12:18.880
We need to make him a traitor.

01:12:19.172 --> 01:12:21.132
Park is only a wild idealist.

01:12:21.716 --> 01:12:26.964
Are you his lawyer? Interrogate
him, not defend him.

01:12:27.300 --> 01:12:28.880
You might regret later.

01:12:29.380 --> 01:12:30.671
What?

01:12:30.672 --> 01:12:34.840
I'm afraid he's planning something

01:12:35.172 --> 01:12:36.592
through the trial.

01:12:37.508 --> 01:12:42.171
Are you saying you're afraid of

01:12:42.172 --> 01:12:44.300
that 'wild idealist'?

01:12:45.880 --> 01:12:47.340
I'll take the responsibility.

01:12:47.672 --> 01:12:51.216
Prosecute him for treason!

01:12:52.256 --> 01:12:54.548
I heard you're on a hunger strike.

01:12:54.924 --> 01:12:56.964
It's not a big deal.

01:12:57.840 --> 01:13:00.424
You'll be charged for treason, right?

01:13:01.132 --> 01:13:02.880
Mr. Lee,

01:13:04.300 --> 01:13:10.008
can you help me make this trial
a headline news back home?

01:13:14.092 --> 01:13:19.840
The rumor says you're a wild idealist.

01:13:20.300 --> 01:13:23.424
Ideals might seem wild at first.

01:13:24.172 --> 01:13:29.048
That's how Koreans have been
educated and brainwashed.

01:13:30.548 --> 01:13:37.008
I want to show something to
our people through this trial.

01:13:41.380 --> 01:13:42.716
I'll try.

01:13:48.008 --> 01:13:50.464
Can you pass my message?

01:13:55.840 --> 01:13:59.340
"I suggest cohabitation.

01:14:01.092 --> 01:14:05.132
First, we live together as comrades.

01:14:05.632 --> 01:14:12.672
Secondly, we're equals in
the anarchist movement.

01:14:13.464 --> 01:14:20.924
Thirdly, cohabitation ends when
either betrays or joins the power".

01:14:22.964 --> 01:14:24.340
You know what this is.

01:14:27.216 --> 01:14:32.339
It's the cohabitation
agreement he and I made

01:14:32.340 --> 01:14:34.508
when we first met.

01:14:40.474 --> 01:14:45.716
"Though we are apart, I'm fully
aware of you by my side.

01:14:46.632 --> 01:14:50.840
I'm strictly abiding by the vow.

01:14:51.300 --> 01:14:59.672
And I have no doubt
you're doing the same".

01:15:02.208 --> 01:15:04.208
A message from Park.

01:15:05.424 --> 01:15:10.340
Any words you have for him?

01:15:13.883 --> 01:15:17.427
That's my boy.

01:15:25.708 --> 01:15:27.415
Thank you for sending my letters

01:15:27.416 --> 01:15:28.792
and letting me eat.

01:15:29.916 --> 01:15:33.080
Oh, Mizuno made this happen?

01:15:34.372 --> 01:15:37.580
Pass my gratitude to him.

01:15:38.622 --> 01:15:42.000
This is psychiatrist Sugita.

01:15:42.332 --> 01:15:44.208
Take a psychiatric test.

01:15:44.748 --> 01:15:46.416
What's wrong with my mind?

01:15:47.956 --> 01:15:53.500
Isn't it natural for us to
want to murder the prince?

01:15:54.372 --> 01:15:55.872
I'm normal!

01:15:58.208 --> 01:15:59.499
What's he saying?

01:15:59.500 --> 01:16:02.872
Never mind. I'll make the decision.

01:16:10.332 --> 01:16:15.663
You pretend to be fair and
conscientious as a lawyer.

01:16:15.664 --> 01:16:17.500
But that's a self-deception.

01:16:17.832 --> 01:16:19.208
Self-deception?

01:16:22.956 --> 01:16:26.624
You shouldn't have invaded Korea

01:16:26.708 --> 01:16:29.708
and massacred our people
in the first place.

01:16:30.124 --> 01:16:32.456
Don't complain that to me.

01:16:35.372 --> 01:16:41.916
What will you do if I refuse the trial?

01:16:46.080 --> 01:16:50.916
But test Fumiko by all means.

01:16:51.580 --> 01:16:53.580
I bet she's pretty crazy.

01:16:56.500 --> 01:16:59.832
Please cooperate with us.

01:17:00.832 --> 01:17:02.164
How does it work?

01:17:02.416 --> 01:17:08.372
Blood test, urine test,
and a few questions.

01:17:10.664 --> 01:17:13.372
What's the reward?

01:17:14.292 --> 01:17:16.500
We'll issue a certificate.

01:17:19.416 --> 01:17:21.956
No cookies or cake?

01:17:26.164 --> 01:17:29.624
- Do you have any?
- Well...

01:17:30.248 --> 01:17:31.292
You don't?

01:17:40.080 --> 01:17:42.832
You are asking for my
blood and urine for free?

01:17:44.748 --> 01:17:47.372
I'd rather be tortured!

01:17:50.219 --> 01:17:51.595
Fuck off!

01:17:55.208 --> 01:17:59.580
Park says he'd refuse the trial.

01:18:00.292 --> 01:18:06.372
This case won't be closed without
having him in the court.

01:18:08.272 --> 01:18:10.980
Park went on a hunger strike again.

01:18:13.448 --> 01:18:16.116
What's the reason this time?

01:18:22.240 --> 01:18:25.240
What's the problem?

01:18:26.032 --> 01:18:29.572
- I want more rice.
- What?

01:18:30.364 --> 01:18:34.948
Koreans eat more rice
than you Japanese do.

01:18:35.656 --> 01:18:39.992
Are you treating me like a Japanese?

01:18:41.992 --> 01:18:44.864
To me, this is very insulting.

01:18:47.448 --> 01:18:50.908
Okay. You'll get as much as you want.

01:18:51.408 --> 01:18:53.200
That's the right thing.

01:18:53.532 --> 01:18:54.992
Happy now?

01:18:56.156 --> 01:18:59.908
Sorry for making you
come and go so often.

01:19:02.948 --> 01:19:09.364
Since you're here, can
you do me another favor?

01:19:09.740 --> 01:19:10.864
Now, what?

01:19:20.240 --> 01:19:21.572
Get dressed.

01:19:24.532 --> 01:19:25.864
What is this?

01:19:26.200 --> 01:19:30.448
Judge Tatematsu must be insane.

01:19:36.864 --> 01:19:37.908
How do I look?

01:19:54.740 --> 01:19:55.740
Park.

01:20:03.908 --> 01:20:05.448
You haven't changed a bit.

01:20:08.532 --> 01:20:11.824
How do I look? Look handsome?

01:20:13.572 --> 01:20:15.532
Even in those new clothes,

01:20:15.780 --> 01:20:19.656
you look shabby just like
the first time we met.

01:20:21.908 --> 01:20:23.656
But you fell for that?

01:20:24.218 --> 01:20:25.386
I did.

01:20:26.864 --> 01:20:30.032
I should've worn Korean
traditional clothes.

01:20:30.948 --> 01:20:34.032
What's all this?

01:20:36.448 --> 01:20:40.740
I want to send a picture of
us to my mother in Korea.

01:20:42.992 --> 01:20:44.492
Your mother?

01:20:58.240 --> 01:21:00.280
Look at the camera.

01:21:13.780 --> 01:21:18.364
Here we go. One, two, three.

01:21:22.200 --> 01:21:24.700
Will you excuse us for a moment?

01:21:28.700 --> 01:21:30.200
All right.

01:21:31.824 --> 01:21:33.992
Let's go, everyone.

01:21:36.116 --> 01:21:38.364
Let's go.

01:21:43.532 --> 01:21:44.532
Thank you.

01:21:44.533 --> 01:21:46.072
Good day, sir.

01:21:51.240 --> 01:21:52.908
You'll regret this.

01:21:58.216 --> 01:22:02.548
It's the Sun that makes you
take off clothes, not the wind.

01:22:04.756 --> 01:22:08.924
It's obvious what they will do in there.

01:22:10.132 --> 01:22:16.340
Why do you always have to think that way?

01:22:16.380 --> 01:22:21.339
Park wanted to send that
picture to his mother

01:22:21.340 --> 01:22:24.132
as a good-bye present.

01:22:28.172 --> 01:22:29.964
Are you feeling sorry for them?

01:22:32.092 --> 01:22:34.232
When I think about Fumiko's childhood,

01:22:35.464 --> 01:22:38.256
I kind of understand why

01:22:38.800 --> 01:22:42.464
she ended up cursing this world.

01:22:50.092 --> 01:22:55.508
Based on the statements
you made until today,

01:22:55.716 --> 01:23:01.631
You'll be charged with treason
in Article 73 of the Criminal Act.

01:23:01.632 --> 01:23:05.548
The next step will take place
at the Supreme Court.

01:23:07.132 --> 01:23:09.092
Treason, finally.

01:23:11.000 --> 01:23:12.208
Good job.

01:23:27.708 --> 01:23:31.164
Are you sure about sending
this to your mother?

01:23:32.708 --> 01:23:34.500
My mother is open-minded.

01:23:37.748 --> 01:23:39.416
I like this picture

01:23:40.080 --> 01:23:43.208
I'll keep a copy.

01:23:45.080 --> 01:23:47.208
Is that a souvenir or a trophy?

01:23:47.456 --> 01:23:53.164
This case gave me an opportunity
to investigate a traitor

01:23:53.248 --> 01:23:56.248
and show my loyalty to my country.

01:23:57.372 --> 01:24:01.456
This is the souvenir of my accomplishment.

01:24:04.164 --> 01:24:09.372
It could be a souvenir to you,
but it will be a trophy to me.

01:24:11.624 --> 01:24:13.416
This is only a beginning.

01:24:14.792 --> 01:24:20.332
These attorneys will
defend you at the court.

01:24:22.248 --> 01:24:23.708
I have some conditions.

01:24:24.956 --> 01:24:30.580
First, I'm not standing in
the court as a defendant.

01:24:31.580 --> 01:24:36.080
The judge at the court is on
behalf of the Japanese emperor

01:24:36.748 --> 01:24:40.748
I'll stand in the court on
behalf of the Korean people.

01:24:41.208 --> 01:24:42.332
Therefore,

01:24:42.456 --> 01:24:48.123
They shall allow me to wear traditional
Korean clothes at the court.

01:24:48.124 --> 01:24:49.791
That's our man, right?

01:24:49.792 --> 01:24:56.664
Secondly, I stand in the court
to condemn Japanese invasion,

01:24:56.792 --> 01:25:01.579
<i>Allow me to read the declaration
to express my thoughts.</i>

01:25:01.580 --> 01:25:04.223
- Will they pass these conditions?
- Park will make it happen.

01:25:04.248 --> 01:25:05.248
Here you go.

01:25:06.000 --> 01:25:10.208
<i>Thirdly, hire an interpreter, for
I will speak Korean at the trial.</i>

01:25:10.372 --> 01:25:11.916
This is all I got.

01:25:12.124 --> 01:25:13.124
<i>Finally,</i>

01:25:13.664 --> 01:25:18.792
<i>let me sit as high as the judge's seat.</i>

01:25:19.580 --> 01:25:21.540
This is nonsense.

01:25:21.872 --> 01:25:25.208
If you don't accept this,
he'll refuse the trial.

01:25:26.416 --> 01:25:31.624
You don't want to see
a traitor refuse the trial.

01:25:31.956 --> 01:25:37.956
The defendant will sit as high as my seat?

01:25:39.416 --> 01:25:41.372
I don't mind losing my face,

01:25:41.708 --> 01:25:46.580
but save the face of
Japanese supreme court

01:25:49.248 --> 01:25:53.164
I'll talk to him to give up one condition.

01:25:59.240 --> 01:26:00.908
Make him give up two.

01:26:01.364 --> 01:26:05.492
I'll withdraw the condition
to speak in Korean,

01:26:05.824 --> 01:26:10.116
to lessen the confusion at the court.

01:26:10.700 --> 01:26:13.780
That's one.

01:26:15.200 --> 01:26:21.240
Can you give up the
condition about the seat?

01:26:23.240 --> 01:26:24.656
Why?

01:26:25.280 --> 01:26:31.116
The judges are afraid that people
will make fun of the situation.

01:26:37.532 --> 01:26:44.447
Okay, but get me Korean traditional
uniform for the d-day.

01:26:44.448 --> 01:26:47.156
Don't worry. I'll get it for you

01:26:47.240 --> 01:26:48.780
I'll do it.

01:26:51.492 --> 01:26:55.656
I'll wear Korean clothes, too.

01:27:01.700 --> 01:27:04.492
One more thing.

01:27:05.364 --> 01:27:11.448
Ask them to accept our
marriage registration.

01:27:13.616 --> 01:27:15.492
Marriage registration?

01:27:18.364 --> 01:27:20.324
We'll receive a death sentence.

01:27:26.448 --> 01:27:27.532
So?

01:27:34.780 --> 01:27:39.072
Bodies can be collected only by family.

01:27:40.492 --> 01:27:45.116
If you become my legal wife,

01:27:46.072 --> 01:27:52.824
my family will collect your body, too.

01:28:01.992 --> 01:28:03.072
Then...?

01:28:08.156 --> 01:28:12.324
We'll be buried together

01:28:13.572 --> 01:28:15.992
in my hometown in Korea.

01:28:22.408 --> 01:28:26.116
<i>I wanted to learn how to write.</i>

01:28:29.408 --> 01:28:35.408
<i>My parents never taught
me a single letter.</i>

01:28:36.864 --> 01:28:41.824
<i>My father didn't care, and
my mother was illiterate.</i>

01:28:45.448 --> 01:28:48.616
<i>In Korea, I was often
kicked out on the road.</i>

01:28:50.440 --> 01:28:54.148
<i>Famished, I staggered on the street</i>

01:28:55.299 --> 01:28:57.923
<i>and found a chunk of burnt rice,</i>

01:28:57.948 --> 01:29:01.364
<i>which I hurriedly put into my mouth.</i>

01:29:03.463 --> 01:29:05.839
<i>My grandma told me,</i>

01:29:05.864 --> 01:29:08.240
<i>"You're a nobody."</i>

01:29:08.824 --> 01:29:14.448
<i>You were born, but you never existed.</i>

01:29:14.700 --> 01:29:17.947
<i>"That's why you can't go to school"</i>

01:29:17.948 --> 01:29:22.324
<i>I will survive. That's right.</i>

01:29:22.940 --> 01:29:28.272
<i>I will take revenge against
those who make us suffer.</i>

01:29:28.980 --> 01:29:33.148
<i>That's right. I shall live.</i>

01:29:36.024 --> 01:29:39.148
<i>I will sacrifice my life to fight for them,</i>

01:29:39.648 --> 01:29:44.400
<i>for isolated people like us.</i>

01:29:44.856 --> 01:29:48.816
<i>February 26th, 1926
First trial</i>

01:29:49.856 --> 01:29:51.108
Line up.

01:29:52.480 --> 01:29:55.856
This does look like a trial for treason.

01:29:56.400 --> 01:30:01.192
Yes, 200 police officers and
30 military police officers.

01:30:02.772 --> 01:30:04.356
Please read this.

01:30:24.192 --> 01:30:26.108
Fumiko!

01:30:27.148 --> 01:30:28.856
You look pretty, Fumiko

01:30:32.232 --> 01:30:36.064
I'm getting a strange
feeling about this trial.

01:30:36.816 --> 01:30:38.856
Tell me about it.

01:31:00.608 --> 01:31:02.815
This is going to be an
extraordinary trial.

01:31:02.816 --> 01:31:04.192
Right, right.

01:31:05.272 --> 01:31:08.147
I'm not at a wedding, am I?

01:31:08.148 --> 01:31:13.692
Are we watching a bride and
groom walking in or what?

01:31:13.772 --> 01:31:18.024
Let's celebrate! Sing along, guys!

01:31:22.732 --> 01:31:26.480
- Now we only need a pastor.
- I know!

01:31:30.564 --> 01:31:32.608
All rise.

01:31:40.108 --> 01:31:41.648
Be seated.

01:31:48.232 --> 01:31:52.023
What the hell are they wearing?

01:31:52.024 --> 01:31:53.564
Shut up!

01:31:55.148 --> 01:31:58.148
Silence!

01:31:58.480 --> 01:31:59.940
Silence!

01:32:00.400 --> 01:32:02.737
Be quiet or we'll ask you to leave.

01:32:03.772 --> 01:32:04.900
Don't be scared.

01:32:05.148 --> 01:32:06.400
Watch me,

01:32:06.772 --> 01:32:10.400
I'll be the most rebellious
defendant in history.

01:32:13.024 --> 01:32:14.356
Name.

01:32:17.064 --> 01:32:18.692
My name is Park Yeol.

01:32:20.764 --> 01:32:23.392
Are you speaking in Korean?

01:32:25.541 --> 01:32:26.892
Yes, I am.

01:32:39.056 --> 01:32:40.432
Name.

01:32:40.764 --> 01:32:42.932
My name is Park Mun-ja.

01:32:44.724 --> 01:32:48.764
- How dare you speak Korean?
- Hang them right away!

01:32:49.100 --> 01:32:52.016
They don't deserve a trial!

01:33:03.680 --> 01:33:09.472
In order to keep the
public order at the court,

01:33:09.808 --> 01:33:12.680
We ask you to leave the gallery at once.

01:33:13.284 --> 01:33:15.808
Leave the courthouse!

01:33:34.432 --> 01:33:36.100
Sir, what does this say?

01:33:37.680 --> 01:33:43.392
This is the number of Koreans massacred
during the big earthquake in Kanto.

01:33:43.848 --> 01:33:45.224
Is this true?

01:33:46.848 --> 01:33:50.599
Yes. The actual number may be even higher

01:33:50.600 --> 01:33:53.724
if you include unconfirmed deaths.

01:34:01.100 --> 01:34:05.016
I believe that Japanese
Empire will collapse.

01:34:05.340 --> 01:34:09.216
Once the false image of a deified Emperor

01:34:09.556 --> 01:34:14.972
is revealed to its people that

01:34:15.556 --> 01:34:18.848
he, too, is only a human being.

01:34:19.140 --> 01:34:23.348
- Shut your mouth!
- You dirty Korean!

01:34:29.472 --> 01:34:34.056
But the Japanese people
do not try to realize that.

01:34:34.432 --> 01:34:37.640
The Empire of Japan will be maintained

01:34:38.264 --> 01:34:44.556
only until you force your people
to believe in Emperor's holiness.

01:34:46.848 --> 01:34:53.056
You managed to distract your people

01:34:53.892 --> 01:34:56.600
whenever you faced a crisis.

01:34:57.640 --> 01:35:02.847
But the time is near for
the fall of the empire.

01:35:02.848 --> 01:35:05.432
You're insane!

01:35:06.556 --> 01:35:08.600
Judge!

01:35:09.472 --> 01:35:15.432
The very devils that destroy
our equal world are

01:35:15.764 --> 01:35:18.472
The Japanese Emperor and the Prince.

01:35:21.100 --> 01:35:25.763
- They demand our sacrifice for the nation...
- You dirty bitch!

01:35:25.764 --> 01:35:27.679
You betrayed Japan.

01:35:27.680 --> 01:35:30.892
Shut The Fuck Up!

01:35:38.180 --> 01:35:44.031
The ruling class demands patriotism

01:35:44.056 --> 01:35:47.224
and loyalty for their interest.

01:35:47.808 --> 01:35:52.991
Their brutal desire is maintained

01:35:53.016 --> 01:35:56.224
by sacrificing people's lives.

01:35:58.909 --> 01:36:00.471
Therefore,

01:36:00.472 --> 01:36:03.516
I warn those who blindly
accept such concepts

01:36:03.892 --> 01:36:09.472
that you will be enslaved unless
you enlighten yourselves.

01:36:14.556 --> 01:36:17.724
Is it a speech contest, or what!?

01:36:18.348 --> 01:36:22.180
Well, I have no right to stop their speech!

01:36:25.348 --> 01:36:28.056
Keep off foreign journalists.

01:36:28.725 --> 01:36:30.517
Mizuno put pressure.

01:36:30.911 --> 01:36:33.579
The second trial will be closed.

01:36:35.380 --> 01:36:37.132
Closed trial...

01:36:37.592 --> 01:36:40.008
You went overboard at the first trial.

01:36:40.380 --> 01:36:42.784
You can't wear the Korean robes anymore.

01:36:44.216 --> 01:36:49.716
Doesn't matter. That will make more news.

01:36:50.216 --> 01:36:54.840
The Great Kanto Earthquake was followed by

01:36:55.164 --> 01:36:58.540
the tragic massacre of
innocent Korean people

01:36:58.880 --> 01:37:05.548
I can't help but doubt that
this case was manipulated

01:37:05.880 --> 01:37:10.132
to cover up the massacre of Korean people.

01:37:10.592 --> 01:37:15.172
On behalf of the highest
authority in Japan,

01:37:15.880 --> 01:37:21.880
Supreme Court must make its
position clear to the entire world.

01:37:22.216 --> 01:37:28.840
Not only for these two, but to
save Japan from such doubts,

01:37:30.124 --> 01:37:34.372
I demand an answer.

01:37:34.840 --> 01:37:37.092
Answer from whom?

01:37:38.380 --> 01:37:44.132
On behalf of Japan,
I ask you to answer it.

01:37:46.924 --> 01:37:48.672
Why should I?

01:37:49.380 --> 01:37:53.632
The emperor can't be summoned
as the witness, can he?

01:37:55.592 --> 01:38:00.132
Will you summon him, if I ask?

01:38:03.092 --> 01:38:04.756
Recess!

01:38:16.565 --> 01:38:17.924
Are you looking for...

01:38:18.924 --> 01:38:20.800
...this?

01:38:21.256 --> 01:38:23.964
How dare you read it
without my permission?

01:38:24.172 --> 01:38:26.756
Now I understand

01:38:27.048 --> 01:38:29.172
what made you different from us.

01:38:29.924 --> 01:38:31.839
Now you know how enlightened I am.

01:38:31.840 --> 01:38:34.672
I'm not a fool like you.

01:38:38.256 --> 01:38:41.440
I corrected some misspelling.

01:38:50.256 --> 01:38:53.464
Among the many emotions
held by Korean people

01:38:53.592 --> 01:38:58.756
their antipathy towards Japan
is deeply rooted in their hearts.

01:39:04.300 --> 01:39:07.008
- What made me who I am now -

01:39:11.632 --> 01:39:18.256
In 1919, March 1st, I witnessed
Korean Independence Movement.

01:39:19.092 --> 01:39:24.592
On that day, I felt a strong
feeling of empathy to Koreans

01:39:25.672 --> 01:39:29.548
and a strong will to rebel against power

01:39:30.424 --> 01:39:32.340
erupted inside me.

01:39:34.622 --> 01:39:35.622
On that day,

01:39:36.832 --> 01:39:40.708
Japanese government cut off our tongues,

01:39:41.040 --> 01:39:42.332
burned our people,

01:39:42.708 --> 01:39:46.956
and stabbed women's
genitals with steel skewers

01:39:47.872 --> 01:39:51.916
and they threatened us
never to mention about.

01:39:52.956 --> 01:39:55.624
March 1st Movement.

01:39:57.792 --> 01:40:05.332
I remember the massacre after
the earthquake in Kanto.

01:40:06.124 --> 01:40:09.372
Koreans were killed with
bamboo spears and swords,

01:40:09.832 --> 01:40:14.624
They were tied and thrown alive

01:40:15.208 --> 01:40:17.792
into the rivers and fire.

01:40:18.124 --> 01:40:27.540
They were tied to bikes and
dragged until they died.

01:40:29.456 --> 01:40:34.456
And you're trying to conceal
the Korean massacre,

01:40:34.832 --> 01:40:39.164
just like March 1st Movement.

01:40:40.580 --> 01:40:42.000
However,

01:40:43.792 --> 01:40:45.832
I will not let that happen.

01:40:46.664 --> 01:40:49.372
The more you try to conceal it,

01:40:49.708 --> 01:40:53.956
the more it'll unveil to the world,

01:40:54.456 --> 01:40:56.248
and to the history.

01:40:58.748 --> 01:41:02.708
You call your country a civilized nation.

01:41:03.416 --> 01:41:07.500
Then conduct an investigation,

01:41:07.832 --> 01:41:11.000
gather witnesses' testimonies

01:41:11.748 --> 01:41:13.975
and dig out the bodies
of innocent Koreans.

01:41:14.000 --> 01:41:19.792
Get confessions from
the soldiers and vigilantes.

01:41:20.332 --> 01:41:26.580
If you still can't find the
truth, yes, I'm a lunatic.

01:41:27.416 --> 01:41:31.000
If you still can't find the truth,

01:41:31.378 --> 01:41:33.347
I'll convert to Japanese Imperialism

01:41:33.372 --> 01:41:37.792
and be a citizen under
your sacred Emperor!

01:41:43.758 --> 01:41:46.594
To protect your emperor,

01:41:46.956 --> 01:41:52.124
over 6,000 of us were
killed without a reason.

01:41:53.580 --> 01:41:55.124
Any objection?

01:41:55.500 --> 01:41:57.372
Get that traitor!

01:42:00.040 --> 01:42:02.080
Please calm down.

01:42:03.664 --> 01:42:06.080
His statement is not true.

01:42:07.208 --> 01:42:10.080
Yes.

01:42:11.956 --> 01:42:16.872
We can't simply believe
such traitor's words...

01:42:17.872 --> 01:42:21.832
This is Mizuno speaking.
Please tell the emperor,

01:42:22.164 --> 01:42:28.080
the cabinet will organize
an investigation committee.

01:42:28.416 --> 01:42:32.540
Tell him not to worry.

01:42:32.872 --> 01:42:34.456
Thank you.

01:42:34.872 --> 01:42:36.872
What investigation committee?

01:42:37.075 --> 01:42:38.535
Yes.

01:42:38.864 --> 01:42:41.532
Japan is a civilized country
with law and order.

01:42:41.864 --> 01:42:45.948
But the committee will be
dissolved after the time limit.

01:42:46.864 --> 01:42:50.572
If we don't give enough time,
there will be fierce criticism.

01:42:51.156 --> 01:42:52.908
I can tell you for sure.

01:42:53.948 --> 01:42:57.700
In a month, they'll want to stop.

01:42:58.156 --> 01:43:01.363
What if they find evidence
within that period?

01:43:01.364 --> 01:43:05.740
The military participated
in the massacre too.

01:43:06.700 --> 01:43:09.780
Holding the military responsible?

01:43:11.864 --> 01:43:14.864
That means blaming his majesty the King!

01:43:16.010 --> 01:43:18.532
So before things get uglier,

01:43:18.824 --> 01:43:24.032
you should end the trial.

01:43:24.364 --> 01:43:28.072
That's why we should throw
Park onto the guillotine

01:43:28.408 --> 01:43:32.026
before the lunatic drives us all insane!!

01:43:34.116 --> 01:43:37.448
You have visitors.

01:43:38.356 --> 01:43:44.064
Novelist Nakanishi and Satomura.

01:43:44.948 --> 01:43:51.740
He was once jailed in Korea for
criticizing the Governor-general.

01:43:52.572 --> 01:43:54.156
How have you been?

01:43:54.492 --> 01:43:56.156
You know each other?

01:43:57.324 --> 01:44:06.364
We fought together against
the abuse of Korean miners.

01:44:07.364 --> 01:44:11.408
On behalf of Japan, I came
to deliver apologies.

01:44:12.410 --> 01:44:19.408
I promise I will make
Japan pay for its faults.

01:44:22.480 --> 01:44:28.608
Please don't forget that
many of us admire you.

01:44:29.356 --> 01:44:35.940
Never give up on conscience
of Japanese people.

01:44:37.692 --> 01:44:41.940
We're Korean students.

01:44:42.232 --> 01:44:45.608
We'll follow your footsteps.

01:44:46.356 --> 01:44:47.524
Thank you.

01:44:48.608 --> 01:44:53.316
I can't run them on papers
anyway, let me get inside, now.

01:44:53.856 --> 01:44:54.804
You sons of bitches!

01:44:54.829 --> 01:44:58.316
<i>March 25th, 1926
The final trial</i>

01:45:00.692 --> 01:45:02.772
All rise.

01:45:12.108 --> 01:45:13.272
What?

01:45:15.232 --> 01:45:16.400
Be seated.

01:45:19.024 --> 01:45:22.692
Prosecutor, please deliver
the closing argument.

01:45:23.692 --> 01:45:27.816
Defendant Park Yeol.

01:45:28.856 --> 01:45:36.440
Having a deprived childhood, he
gradually developed a grudge.

01:45:36.772 --> 01:45:38.232
<i>We'll never forget!</i>

01:45:38.564 --> 01:45:42.608
<i>We'll reveal the truth!</i>

01:45:42.940 --> 01:45:48.192
We will never forget!

01:45:48.772 --> 01:45:50.692
<i>We'll never forget!</i>

01:45:52.564 --> 01:45:54.940
<i>We'll reveal the truth!</i>

01:45:56.940 --> 01:46:04.148
He became obsessed with narrow
political and social views.

01:46:06.232 --> 01:46:08.063
Kaneko Fumiko had tragic childhood

01:46:08.064 --> 01:46:12.856
and her parents abandoned her.

01:46:13.232 --> 01:46:16.856
She denied power and authority...

01:46:17.356 --> 01:46:19.108
<i>We'll never forget!</i>

01:46:21.732 --> 01:46:23.816
<i>We'll reveal the truth!</i>

01:46:27.863 --> 01:46:34.071
According to Article 238,
the two are found jointly guilty.

01:46:34.400 --> 01:46:37.608
Henceforth, they will be prosecuted
according to the sentencing.

01:46:42.608 --> 01:46:45.148
Defendants, any last word?

01:46:45.816 --> 01:46:49.272
No. Good job.

01:46:53.772 --> 01:46:57.900
Kaneko Fumiko, any last word?

01:47:04.116 --> 01:47:11.908
I know Park's true nature.

01:47:13.692 --> 01:47:16.108
And I love him the way he is.

01:47:17.564 --> 01:47:23.692
Despite all his shortcomings,
I embrace every single part of it.

01:47:25.316 --> 01:47:29.192
I truly love him as he is.

01:47:35.980 --> 01:47:38.148
This is my request to the court.

01:47:41.192 --> 01:47:45.940
Throw us onto the guillotine together.

01:47:47.064 --> 01:47:51.856
I'll be happy as long as I die with him.

01:47:52.385 --> 01:47:54.925
Shut up! Close the trial!

01:47:57.440 --> 01:47:59.064
Lastly,

01:48:01.772 --> 01:48:03.524
my last word to Park.

01:48:05.856 --> 01:48:11.772
Even if the sentence separates us,

01:48:14.732 --> 01:48:16.108
I will

01:48:20.732 --> 01:48:22.108
never

01:48:24.148 --> 01:48:31.480
leave you to die alone.

01:48:45.732 --> 01:48:49.564
For treason in Article
73 of the Criminal Act

01:48:49.900 --> 01:48:54.692
and for violating the
explosives regulation,

01:48:54.980 --> 01:48:59.524
I hereby announce the sentence.

01:49:00.613 --> 01:49:04.781
Park Yeol and Kaneko Fumiko

01:49:05.221 --> 01:49:07.345
are sentenced to death.

01:49:12.980 --> 01:49:14.564
Hey, Judge.

01:49:16.272 --> 01:49:17.732
Hey, Judge!

01:49:20.732 --> 01:49:24.192
You can do whatever you want with my body,

01:49:24.524 --> 01:49:28.480
but you can do nothing to my spirit.

01:49:28.816 --> 01:49:30.480
Hurray!

01:49:32.732 --> 01:49:34.856
Hurray!

01:49:35.564 --> 01:49:37.524
Hurray!

01:49:45.400 --> 01:49:48.439
<i>Traitors Sentenced to Death.</i>

01:49:48.440 --> 01:49:51.772
"Fumiko sadly lowered her head?"

01:49:54.064 --> 01:49:56.979
What's wrong with these articles?
This isn't true at all.

01:49:56.980 --> 01:50:01.064
<i>Park cursed and swore at the judge?</i>

01:50:02.816 --> 01:50:06.939
When did he curse at the judge?
This is insane.

01:50:06.940 --> 01:50:08.524
Sons of bitches.

01:50:09.651 --> 01:50:11.993
There's an article on a Korean Daily.

01:50:18.848 --> 01:50:22.079
Only Korean Daily told truth
about the hurraying.

01:50:22.104 --> 01:50:24.056
<i>Screams Hurray after
Hearing the Death Sentence.</i>

01:50:26.140 --> 01:50:32.391
The parliament is against
the death sentence.

01:50:32.392 --> 01:50:35.556
We held trials to cover up the massacre,

01:50:35.892 --> 01:50:41.100
and we finally sentenced them to death.

01:50:42.180 --> 01:50:45.640
If the imperial family
reduces the sentence now,

01:50:46.056 --> 01:50:53.224
that will make this trial
look like that rebel's circus.

01:50:54.056 --> 01:50:57.100
What do you think,
Governor-general of Korea?

01:50:58.224 --> 01:51:02.931
We suppressed the March 1st
Movement with great difficulty

01:51:02.932 --> 01:51:11.056
I'm afraid what will happen
in Korea when we execute him.

01:51:11.392 --> 01:51:15.892
Koreans are all fixing
their eyes on this trial.

01:51:16.308 --> 01:51:17.808
In that case,

01:51:17.972 --> 01:51:22.224
we have to make a political choice.

01:51:42.392 --> 01:51:47.180
Emperor reduced your sentence

01:51:48.764 --> 01:51:50.224
to life sentence.

01:52:02.640 --> 01:52:06.140
<i>Letter of Mercy</i>

01:52:08.892 --> 01:52:14.724
Emperor? Who gave him such a right?

01:52:18.640 --> 01:52:26.556
The supreme court's death
sentence was fair enough,

01:52:26.892 --> 01:52:38.516
Nevertheless, the imperial
family decided to show mercy.

01:52:38.724 --> 01:52:45.680
Accordingly, the death penalty
is reduced to life imprisonment.

01:52:46.808 --> 01:52:51.016
<i>Letter of Mercy Accepted
with Deep Gratitude</i>

01:52:59.812 --> 01:53:03.489
You'll be transported
to the prison in Chiba.

01:53:06.749 --> 01:53:08.209
How about Fumiko?

01:53:08.556 --> 01:53:11.016
She'll be transported to Utsunomiya.

01:53:12.180 --> 01:53:14.516
A distant place from Chiba.

01:53:26.600 --> 01:53:28.764
Please take care of these.

01:53:30.100 --> 01:53:34.472
Keep the sentences simple and candid.

01:53:34.909 --> 01:53:37.865
Don't worry too much about the grammar.

01:53:39.035 --> 01:53:42.743
I don't want poetic phrases
or fancy adjectives.

01:53:46.056 --> 01:53:47.348
Okay.

01:53:49.923 --> 01:53:52.892
I promise you I will publish them.

01:54:01.196 --> 01:54:03.072
Pass my love to the members.

01:54:24.140 --> 01:54:26.848
<i>Family Register</i>

01:54:29.600 --> 01:54:33.556
Head of family, Park Yeol.

01:55:01.640 --> 01:55:06.932
<i>Chiba Prison</i>

01:55:17.142 --> 01:55:23.348
<i>To Live doesn't merely mean To Move.</i>

01:55:25.467 --> 01:55:28.343
<i>If I can move upon my will,</i>

01:55:31.716 --> 01:55:37.800
<i>even if the move itself
eventually leads to Death,</i>

01:55:39.964 --> 01:55:44.592
<i>It is not the denial of Life.</i>

01:55:45.548 --> 01:55:47.800
<i>It is an Affirmation.</i>

01:55:50.592 --> 01:55:54.340
<i>Only the last 3 years of my life with Park</i>

01:55:55.048 --> 01:56:00.800
<i>was the true life of my own.</i>

01:56:06.172 --> 01:56:08.340
Still on a hunger strike?

01:56:11.632 --> 01:56:17.216
Now I can see the door to the end.

01:56:19.048 --> 01:56:22.300
Please survive.

01:56:25.672 --> 01:56:28.380
How's Fumiko doing?

01:56:31.840 --> 01:56:33.300
You must survive.

01:56:38.092 --> 01:56:44.132
She promised to die with me.

01:56:45.800 --> 01:56:51.132
She said she'd not let me go alone.

01:56:54.228 --> 01:56:56.144
How's Fumiko?

01:57:05.216 --> 01:57:09.592
Tell me. How's she doing?

01:57:14.351 --> 01:57:15.643
She's dead.

01:57:21.364 --> 01:57:22.988
Suicide?

01:57:24.091 --> 01:57:29.219
They won't tell me the cause of her
death, or let me collect her body.

01:57:30.300 --> 01:57:37.256
I couldn't even talk with
the medical examiner.

01:57:41.508 --> 01:57:45.632
You must survive.

01:57:47.644 --> 01:57:49.312
Please bury her

01:57:49.380 --> 01:57:54.756
in my hometown.

01:58:18.713 --> 01:58:25.213
Maybe they killed her
and faked it as suicide.

01:58:26.916 --> 01:58:31.956
She could've killed herself

01:58:33.938 --> 01:58:36.314
to show her resistance against power.

01:58:37.208 --> 01:58:40.664
She must be cold.

01:58:50.500 --> 01:58:53.624
She wrote 1,000 pages
for her autobiography.

01:58:53.832 --> 01:58:57.916
It's nonsense she killed
herself without a note.

01:59:17.124 --> 01:59:20.332
<i>The Asahi Daily</i>

01:59:20.748 --> 01:59:22.787
- You're a journalist, right?
- Yes.

01:59:22.872 --> 01:59:24.500
Have you seen this?

01:59:30.803 --> 01:59:33.931
The Prosecutor let them
use an interrogation room

01:59:33.956 --> 01:59:36.956
and allowed them to take
a picture like this?

01:59:37.080 --> 01:59:40.499
Rumors say Fumiko was murdered.

01:59:40.500 --> 01:59:43.146
She had a sign of strangulation.

01:59:43.506 --> 01:59:44.747
Murder?

01:59:44.748 --> 01:59:47.371
If she had been pregnant,

01:59:47.372 --> 01:59:48.956
they can't let her live.

01:59:49.332 --> 01:59:52.208
They can't let her
give birth in the cell...

01:59:52.992 --> 01:59:57.532
She had a sign of strangulation.
Any evidence for murder?

01:59:57.557 --> 02:00:00.557
Evidence can be manipulated after death.

02:00:00.864 --> 02:00:04.780
This photo was sent to all
the publishing companies.

02:00:05.200 --> 02:00:08.464
Shouldn't we print this first?

02:00:21.656 --> 02:00:24.572
Did you plan this too?

02:00:28.908 --> 02:00:31.280
What are you talking about?

02:00:32.032 --> 02:00:37.116
I couldn't even get a bomb and throw it

02:00:37.448 --> 02:00:40.324
I should do something bigger.

02:00:40.740 --> 02:00:47.908
Keep mocking, but that
won't destroy Japan.

02:00:49.116 --> 02:00:54.032
Keep concealing, but that
won't hide the truth.

02:00:54.616 --> 02:01:01.324
Because you keep digging,
we're becoming more thorough.

02:01:04.408 --> 02:01:08.864
Right, you're thoroughly
making fabulous errors,

02:01:09.780 --> 02:01:15.032
one error after another, and another...

02:01:17.072 --> 02:01:19.240
Will you be able to handle them?

02:01:29.780 --> 02:01:33.032
Do you know why we reduced your sentence?

02:01:35.448 --> 02:01:40.656
To make you be forgotten
and be worthlessly alive.

02:01:43.780 --> 02:01:48.572
To make you live forever in prison.

02:01:49.740 --> 02:01:53.616
Live long, as long as possible,

02:01:55.072 --> 02:01:58.240
and finally make yourself famous for that!

02:02:04.324 --> 02:02:06.156
Of course I will!

02:02:06.780 --> 02:02:09.156
I'll live as long as I can,

02:02:09.492 --> 02:02:15.364
to reveal every single
thing you did to us!

02:02:37.740 --> 02:02:40.408
This could be our last photo.

02:02:40.864 --> 02:02:43.448
Shouldn't we make this special?

02:02:44.280 --> 02:02:46.324
Last photo?

02:02:54.864 --> 02:02:57.032
It shouldn't be ordinary.

02:02:57.419 --> 02:02:58.755
Of course, not.

02:02:58.780 --> 02:03:00.656
This picture will show them

02:03:00.908 --> 02:03:03.572
who we truly are.

02:04:09.240 --> 02:04:15.031
<i>Park served 22 years and 2 months and
was released after Korean Independence.</i>

02:04:15.032 --> 02:04:18.991
<i>In 1946, he excavated the remains of those
who fought for Korean Independence,</i>

02:04:18.992 --> 02:04:21.655
<i>and buried them in Seoul.</i>

02:04:21.656 --> 02:04:30.032
<i>In 1989, Park was posthumously
honored a Presidential Medal.</i>

02:04:30.948 --> 02:04:34.907
<i>Kaneko Fumiko was buried in Korea
in 1931 as Park had wished.</i>

02:04:34.908 --> 02:04:38.699
<i>Kazuo published Fumiko's autobiography.</i>

02:04:38.700 --> 02:04:42.390
<i>Huse, who defended Park
and Fumiko was the first.</i>

02:04:42.415 --> 02:04:46.556
<i>Japanese to be honored Order
of Merit in Korea in 2004</i>

